Judul: NASA DRONE TO SOAR ACROSS TITAN
Abstrak:
NASA will send a dual-quadcopter drone to hop across the surface of Titan, Saturn’s largest moon, the agency announced on 27 June. Named Dragonfly, the US$850-million
mission will launch in 2026 and arrive at Titan in mid-2034. The nuclear-powered drone
(pictured, artist’s impression) could traverse hundreds of kilometres during its two-year
mission
